00:45:42,835 --> 00:45:43,324
Come here.

550
00:45:45,838 --> 00:45:47,237
Very good decision.

551
00:45:49,475 --> 00:45:51,443
I'm so happy.

552
00:45:52,711 --> 00:45:55,236
Babe, what just happened in there?

553
00:45:55,314 --> 00:45:57,612
- What do you mean?
- I mean...

554
00:45:58,117 --> 00:45:59,852
This ring...

555
00:45:59,852 --> 00:46:01,251
I got it for my mom.

556
00:46:03,255 --> 00:46:05,052
It's her birthday gift.

557
00:46:05,657 --> 00:46:06,715
This is for your mom?

558
00:46:07,359 --> 00:46:10,226
Look at it sweety...
it's a mummy ring.

559
00:46:10,295 --> 00:46:11,697
What?

560
00:46:11,697 --> 00:46:13,062
Why didn't you say something?

561
00:46:13,532 --> 00:46:15,056
I tried.

562
00:46:15,134 --> 00:46:19,036
But you were excited and screaming.
And Tanya made an announcement.

563
00:46:19,705 --> 00:46:21,866
So you don't want to marry me?

564
00:46:22,307 --> 00:46:25,834
It's not about you.
I haven't even thought about marriage.

565
00:46:28,514 --> 00:46:30,311
What do I tell my father?

566
00:46:35,287 --> 00:46:38,190
We'll say that
we gave it some more thought and...

567
00:46:38,190 --> 00:46:40,590
we need more time.
That's all.

568
00:46:40,659 --> 00:46:42,286
This is so embarrassing.

569
00:46:43,128 --> 00:46:45,187
I'm so sorry, sweety.

570
00:46:46,131 --> 00:46:48,827
You don't ever want to marry me?

571
00:46:50,102 --> 00:46:51,937
It's not like that.

572
00:46:51,937 --> 00:46:54,462
If it is, you better tell me right now!

573
00:46:55,774 --> 00:46:58,477
I really love you, Kabir.
And I don't...

574
00:46:58,477 --> 00:47:01,708
No, no... no sweety.
Don't cry.

575
00:47:01,780 --> 00:47:02,712
Not now.

576
00:47:10,088 --> 00:47:10,816
Kabir...

577
00:47:12,758 --> 00:47:16,455
are you even serious
about this relationship or not?

578
00:47:19,798 --> 00:47:20,628
You know what...

579
00:47:31,677 --> 00:47:32,701
Will you marry me?

580
00:47:56,835 --> 00:47:57,893
Who is it?

581
00:48:12,784 --> 00:48:13,648
Room service.

582
00:48:14,853 --> 00:48:15,478
Laila?

583
00:48:16,521 --> 00:48:17,545
Hi!

584
00:48:17,623 --> 00:48:18,453
Oh my God!

585
00:48:19,858 --> 00:48:21,325
You're here... how... I mean...

586
00:48:21,760 --> 00:48:24,456
Imran called and
he begged me to come.

587
00:48:24,796 --> 00:48:25,990
- So I came.
- Imran?

588
00:48:26,465 --> 00:48:27,489
I knew it.

589
00:48:28,166 --> 00:48:29,724
He is my best friend.

590
00:48:32,871 --> 00:48:35,032
I am... so glad you're here.

591
00:48:36,475 --> 00:48:38,136
I'm glad you are glad.

592
00:48:40,812 --> 00:48:42,973
Hello... my the two the love the birds!

593
00:48:43,448 --> 00:48:44,779
Hello!

594
00:48:44,917 --> 00:48:45,975
Surprised, Arjun?

595
00:48:47,286 --> 00:48:48,344
Thank you.

596
00:48:48,420 --> 00:48:49,821
It's good to see you.

597
00:48:49,821 --> 00:48:51,015
- And you.
- Hey gorgeous.

598
00:48:51,089 --> 00:48:53,158
- I love you too.
- Nice to have you back.

599
00:48:53,158 --> 00:48:54,523
You got a tan!

600
00:48:55,294 --> 00:48:56,295
Get dressed, soon!

601
00:48:56,295 --> 00:48:57,629
- We had to leave at seven.
- Correct.

602
00:48:57,629 --> 00:48:58,830
- Two minutes?
- You missed me?

603
00:48:58,830 --> 00:49:00,499
I always miss you, darling.

604
00:49:00,499 --> 00:49:01,523
Where are we going?

605
00:49:01,600 --> 00:49:03,227
It's a surprise.
Can't tell you in front of him.

606
00:49:21,286 --> 00:49:22,446
What's going on?

607
00:49:22,854 --> 00:49:23,912
What do you mean?

608
00:49:24,156 --> 00:49:25,214
It's San Fermin.

609
00:49:25,290 --> 00:49:26,325
Running with the bulls.

610
00:49:26,325 --> 00:49:27,724
- Really?
- Didrt you know?

611
00:49:27,793 --> 00:49:28,919
Just follow me...

612
00:49:37,202 --> 00:49:38,260
Holy shit!

613
00:49:45,310 --> 00:49:46,937
Are these guys mad?
What are they doing?

614
00:49:47,179 --> 00:49:47,975
Suicide.

615
00:49:48,513 --> 00:49:49,878
Isn't that why you are here?

616
00:50:00,592 --> 00:50:02,651
I felt this should be the
last experience of our trip.

617
00:50:03,362 --> 00:50:05,830
This could be the
last experience of our life!

618
00:50:06,164 --> 00:50:08,333
Stop it, Arjun.
Let's grab a bite.

619
00:50:08,333 --> 00:50:08,890
Come on.

620
00:50:09,968 --> 00:50:11,036
- Excuse me.
- Dude are you...

621
00:50:11,036 --> 00:50:12,264
- I'm starving!

622
00:50:13,872 --> 00:50:15,362
This is not an adventure sport.

623
00:50:16,041 --> 00:50:17,338
I object, Judge sahab!

624
00:50:17,976 --> 00:50:20,145
I agree it's not as safe as regular sports.

625
00:50:20,145 --> 00:50:21,713
And is illegal in some countries.

626
00:50:21,713 --> 00:50:24,511
But according to the
Spanish tradition and culture...

627
00:50:24,583 --> 00:50:25,517
it is allowed.

628
00:50:25,517 --> 00:50:27,508
And technically,
according to our deal...

629
00:50:27,586 --> 00:50:29,986
we can choose any sport, remember?

630
00:50:30,322 --> 00:50:31,823
Lmran, it's really dangerous, you know.

631
00:50:31,823 --> 00:50:34,018
Yes, those bulls could kill us, alright?

632
00:50:34,259 --> 00:50:36,928
We'll be dangling on their horns
like tandoori chicken on skewers!

633
00:50:36,928 --> 00:50:38,657
Precisely the point.

634
00:50:39,798 --> 00:50:41,857
You want to get rid of
the fear within you?

635
00:50:42,134 --> 00:50:44,295
Well then, here's
our deepest fear. Death.

636
00:50:45,337 --> 00:50:46,361
Let's face it.

637
00:50:46,972 --> 00:50:48,340
Because beyond this fear...

638
00:50:48,340 --> 00:50:49,238
lies victory!

639
00:50:49,307 --> 00:50:51,332
Please spare us the tag lines!

640
00:50:51,777 --> 00:50:53,472
Dude, think about it!

641
00:50:53,712 --> 00:50:57,341
No training, no instructors.
Just us, my amigos!

642
00:50:58,083 --> 00:50:59,880
And some bulls running after us.

643
00:51:00,118 --> 00:51:02,416
If you want to live... just run!

644
00:51:02,821 --> 00:51:04,982
Laila, do you know
any psychiatrist around here?

645
00:51:05,757 --> 00:51:07,987
Because our amigo has
completely lost it!

646
00:51:08,827 --> 00:51:10,852
I'll be at the starting line
at seven tomorrow morning.

647
00:51:11,496 --> 00:51:13,464
With or without you.

648
00:51:19,004 --> 00:51:19,404
I have something for you, lmran.

649
00:51:19,404 --> 00:51:20,393
I have something for you, lmran.

650
00:51:21,273 --> 00:51:22,103
It's from Nuria.

651
00:51:25,877 --> 00:51:26,673
It's in Spanish.

652
00:51:27,646 --> 00:51:28,908
Love has no language.

653
00:51:29,514 --> 00:51:30,208
So true.

654
00:51:33,251 --> 00:51:34,582
I think you should
buy her something.

655
00:51:35,420 --> 00:51:36,250
You're absolutely right.

656
00:51:36,822 --> 00:51:38,380
Guys... next stop - shopping.

657
00:51:39,825 --> 00:51:41,383
Count me out,
I'm going back to the hotel.

658
00:51:42,461 --> 00:51:43,587
Are you alright?

659
00:51:45,964 --> 00:51:46,794
I'm fine.

660
00:51:47,666 --> 00:51:49,634
That we'll only know after a test.

661
00:51:50,502 --> 00:51:51,298
Test?

662
00:51:52,537 --> 00:51:53,765
What do you say, Dr. Fraud?

663
00:51:54,673 --> 00:51:55,367
Are you game?

664
00:51:55,974 --> 00:51:56,702
Bring it on.

665
00:51:57,375 --> 00:51:58,569
You have to say the first thing...

666
00:51:58,643 --> 00:52:00,611
I know the drill. Ask!

667
00:52:01,513 --> 00:52:02,241
Black.

668
00:52:02,481 --> 00:52:03,038
Night.

669
00:52:03,115 --> 00:52:03,979
Sea.

670
00:52:04,149 --> 00:52:04,877
Salty.

671
00:52:04,950 --> 00:52:05,784
Work.

672
00:52:05,784 --> 00:52:06,785
Money.

673
00:52:06,785 --> 00:52:07,649
Sex.

674
00:52:07,853 --> 00:52:08,687
I like!

675
00:52:08,687 --> 00:52:09,210
Friend.

676
00:52:09,588 --> 00:52:10,316
You.

677
00:52:10,522 --> 00:52:11,489
Marriage.

678
00:52:12,824 --> 00:52:13,984
Family.

679
00:52:20,832 --> 00:52:21,662
What?

680
00:52:23,468 --> 00:52:24,970
Is that all?

681
00:52:24,970 --> 00:52:26,267
It was enough.

682
00:52:28,140 --> 00:52:29,808
Smartass...

683
00:52:29,808 --> 00:52:33,505
You're using my trick on me?
Just say what you want to.

684
00:52:34,045 --> 00:52:34,943
Okay.

685
00:52:35,680 --> 00:52:38,080
You hesitated on 'marriage'.

686
00:52:38,517 --> 00:52:39,916
So?

687
00:52:39,985 --> 00:52:43,443
I'm just saying...
you hesitated... on marriage.

688
00:52:47,425 --> 00:52:48,289
Look...

689
00:52:49,294 --> 00:52:52,821
I don't have the time for this crap.
See you later.

690
00:52:56,601 --> 00:52:59,229
- Okay.
- I'm sorry, I'm going to...

691
00:53:07,145 --> 00:53:08,112
Kabir.

692
00:53:13,251 --> 00:53:14,047
Go!

693
00:53:16,955 --> 00:53:18,081
Kabir!

694
00:53:19,090 --> 00:53:20,557
Kabir... man, just stop!

695
00:53:21,259 --> 00:53:22,385
What?

696
00:53:23,495 --> 00:53:25,360
Talk to us man.
What's going on?

697
00:53:25,764 --> 00:53:27,629
It's nothing, really.

698
00:53:29,601 --> 00:53:30,568
Kabir...

699
00:53:32,537 --> 00:53:34,835
Look, I'm sorry I lost my cool.

700
00:53:36,141 --> 00:53:38,473
Because I said you have
a problem with marriage?

701
00:53:39,344 --> 00:53:42,609
I guess, I'm freaking out.
I don't know what's happening.

702
00:53:43,014 --> 00:53:45,350
It's normal to be nervous.

703
00:53:45,350 --> 00:53:47,852
It's not like you're having
an arranged marriage.

704
00:53:47,852 --> 00:53:50,514
Yeah, but she isn't
the same person I met.

705
00:53:51,189 --> 00:53:53,350
She's changed,
she's become possessive.

706
00:53:53,959 --> 00:53:57,258
The girl I knew was a
talented, independent interior designer.

707
00:53:57,429 --> 00:53:59,464
She enjoyed her work.

708
00:53:59,464 --> 00:54:00,431
But now...

709
00:54:00,999 --> 00:54:02,967
she's bid adieu to her passion and...

710
00:54:03,201 --> 00:54:05,101
taken over my life.

711
00:54:06,037 --> 00:54:08,039
Of course, I want a partner but...

712
00:54:08,039 --> 00:54:09,734
I want my own life too!

713
00:54:10,041 --> 00:54:13,841
The whole two bodies, one soul thing
I won't be able to handle it.

714
00:54:24,522 --> 00:54:26,513
- May I ask you something?
- Yes.

715
00:54:27,826 --> 00:54:30,056
Don't you think
you proposed to her too soon?

716
00:54:30,795 --> 00:54:32,964
Actually, I didn't even propose.

717
00:54:32,964 --> 00:54:34,532
- What?

718
00:54:34,532 --> 00:54:36,864
I'd bought a ring for my mom
as a birthday gift.

719
00:54:37,135 --> 00:54:40,536
Before giving it, I happened to show
it to Natasha and she thought...

720
00:54:40,972 --> 00:54:42,439
it was meant for her.

721
00:54:44,209 --> 00:54:45,904
- Are you crazy?
- What are you doing?

722
00:54:46,378 --> 00:54:48,175
- What's wrong with him?
- What's wrong with him?

723
00:54:53,485 --> 00:54:55,851
No wonder this vacation was
so important for you.

724
00:54:56,588 --> 00:54:57,247
Meaning?

725
00:54:58,356 --> 00:55:01,587
Basically, you wanted to hear from someone else
that you shouldn't get married

726
00:55:01,793 --> 00:55:04,496
And besides us,
who would've told you this.

727
00:55:04,496 --> 00:55:06,364
Have you totally lost it?

728
00:55:06,364 --> 00:55:09,026
The invites are printed.
This isn't the time to overreact!

729
00:55:10,001 --> 00:55:10,968
Kabir.

730
00:55:12,504 --> 00:55:14,165
We know Natasha is a great girl.

731
00:55:14,439 --> 00:55:16,407
And we know you like her.

732
00:55:16,941 --> 00:55:18,431
And of course,
you don't want to hurt her.

733
00:55:19,477 --> 00:55:22,446
But ask yourself...
Do you really want to marry her?

734
00:55:23,181 --> 00:55:24,842
And if not, be honest.

735
00:55:24,916 --> 00:55:26,406
To yourself and to her.

736
00:55:27,118 --> 00:55:30,019
Of course, she'll be hurt.
But in the long run its best for both of you.

737
00:55:30,188 --> 00:55:31,815
He is absolutely right, Kabir.

738
00:55:32,090 --> 00:55:33,887
But I've made a commitment.

739
00:55:34,259 --> 00:55:35,994
Okay, you screwed up.

740
00:55:35,994 --> 00:55:38,019
No one's going to send you to prison.

741
00:55:38,096 --> 00:55:40,656
It's not that simple.
Our parents are involved.

742
00:55:40,865 --> 00:55:41,695
Parents?

743
00:55:42,133 --> 00:55:43,259
Dude, it's your life.

744
00:55:46,338 --> 00:55:47,669
You won't get it.

745
00:55:48,840 --> 00:55:49,670
Just...

746
00:55:50,342 --> 00:55:52,503
Just let it be, okay?
I'm sorry.

747
00:55:53,345 --> 00:55:54,471
Kabir...

748
00:55:58,249 --> 00:55:59,216
What a guy!

749
00:56:17,469 --> 00:56:18,493
Laila?

750
00:56:22,440 --> 00:56:23,464
Why're you shouting?

751
00:56:24,542 --> 00:56:26,169
Why are you so far?

752
00:56:40,458 --> 00:56:41,356
Better?

753
00:56:42,694 --> 00:56:43,524
Best.

754
00:56:46,598 --> 00:56:47,326
Ammi?

755
00:56:48,466 --> 00:56:49,933
How are you?

756
00:56:52,837 --> 00:56:54,805
I met Salman.

757
00:57:01,179 --> 00:57:04,205
I now know why you and Abu
kept this from me.

758
00:57:07,819 --> 00:57:08,877
I'm sorry, Ammi.

759
00:57:11,823 --> 00:57:12,881
- I love you.

760
00:57:14,659 --> 00:57:16,183
I love you too, my boy.

761
00:57:52,497 --> 00:57:55,955
It took a while but

762
00:58:00,872 --> 00:58:05,275
I've now learnt to live

763
00:58:09,747 --> 00:58:13,444
Without the consolation of tears

764
00:58:18,122 --> 00:58:22,786
I've now learnt to live

765
00:58:42,680 --> 00:58:49,354
There is someone who brought to mind

766
00:58:49,354 --> 00:58:53,916
How I had gotten left behind

767
00:58:55,660 --> 00:59:01,326
Life is like a caravan

768
00:59:02,467 --> 00:59:06,426
Why are you lonely, my man

769
00:59:08,840 --> 00:59:13,300
Just know that we are all here

770
00:59:36,501 --> 00:59:39,561
The first rocket indicates that
the pen gates have been opened.

771
00:59:39,971 --> 00:59:42,439
Second rocket indicates that
the bulls are coming towards us.

772
00:59:42,774 --> 00:59:44,475
We run at the second rocket.

773
00:59:44,475 --> 00:59:45,339
Second rocket.

774
00:59:46,978 --> 00:59:48,536
Oh San Fermin, please protect us.

775
00:59:50,481 --> 00:59:51,812
If I die...

776
00:59:52,183 --> 00:59:53,912
my spirit will come back to haunt you.

777
00:59:54,352 --> 00:59:55,876
Why are you thinking about death?

778
00:59:55,954 --> 00:59:57,922
Think about what you'll do
if you survive.

779
01:00:02,493 --> 01:00:02,982
Listen...

780
01:00:03,661 --> 01:00:04,559
a new pact.

781
01:00:05,430 --> 01:00:07,125
An if-l-get out-alive pact.

782
01:00:08,299 --> 01:00:10,859
If I get out alive,
I'll let you read my poetry.

783
01:00:12,036 --> 01:00:13,538
Why just you? I'll just...

784
01:00:13,538 --> 01:00:14,732
get it published.

785
01:00:15,607 --> 01:00:16,574
You write poetry?

786
01:00:16,808 --> 01:00:17,638
Yes.

787
01:00:19,444 --> 01:00:20,411
Okay.

788
01:00:20,712 --> 01:00:22,543
If I get out alive...

789
01:00:25,617 --> 01:00:26,311
Okay!

790
01:00:26,784 --> 01:00:28,620
If I get out alive...

791
01:00:28,620 --> 01:00:30,655
I'll go to Morocco with Laila.

792
01:00:30,655 --> 01:00:31,485
Yeah!

793
01:00:31,823 --> 01:00:32,847
That's what I'll do.

794
01:00:33,257 --> 01:00:35,426
What's the worst that could happen?
I'll get fired.

795
01:00:35,426 --> 01:00:36,427
- Right?
- Yeah.

796
01:00:36,427 --> 01:00:37,629
Who cares man?

797
01:00:37,629 --> 01:00:38,823
I'll be with her and I will live.

798
01:00:39,197 --> 01:00:40,357
Well done, my bro!

799
01:00:41,366 --> 01:00:42,196
Come on, Kabir.

800
01:00:44,602 --> 01:00:45,269
Okay.

801
01:00:45,269 --> 01:00:46,964
If I get out alive...

802
01:00:51,109 --> 01:00:52,667
Shit guys!
The gates are open!

803
01:00:53,011 --> 01:00:54,069
Kabir just say it.

804
01:00:54,145 --> 01:00:55,840
It's okay, just say it.

805
01:01:03,121 --> 01:01:05,957
If I get out alive,
I'll go to London...

806
01:01:05,957 --> 01:01:07,686
and tell Natasha that...

807
01:01:17,502 --> 01:01:18,901
Say what?
Just say it!

808
01:01:19,170 --> 01:01:20,398
Come on, Kabir!

809
01:01:24,375 --> 01:01:26,275
- Come on, Kabir!
- Come on!

810
01:01:26,344 --> 01:01:28,938
I'm sorry but I can't marry you.

811
01:01:31,149 --> 01:01:31,816
- Congratulations!
- Look out!

812
01:01:31,816 --> 01:01:33,044
- Congratulations!
- Look out!

